article.headline: New Orleans 80, Louisiana College 46
article.story: NEW ORLEANS -- Zach Kinsley scored 21 points to lead New Orleans to an 80-46 victory over Louisiana College on Wednesday. Tyson Roach added 10 points as the Privateers (3-1) avenged an 81-78 loss to Louisiana College (1-3) on Nov. 18. Kinsley's layup capped a 15-0 run as New Orleans jumped out to a 32-9 lead with 5:55 left in the first half. The Privateers outshot the Wildcats, a Division III program, from the field in the first half -- 53.3 percent (16 of 30) to 28.6 percent (6 of 21) -- to take a 44-17 halftime lead. Kinsley finished the first half with 15 points. New Orleans led by 35 points with 5:18 left in the game. Twelve players saw action and 10 scored for the Privateers. Romanski Williams led Louisiana College, which shot 15 for 53 from the field (28.3 percent) for the game, with 10 points.
